create a basic sse endpoint where client get server events
  - url: /sse
  - server can send events to the client: currently just ping user every 10 seconds
  - also echo each 10 seconds as a demo event

---
Changes:
  chttp.h
  - SseHandler typedef (void (*)(int fd))
  - sse_handler field in Route
  - chttp_sse_route() + CHTTP_SSE() macro
  - chttp_sse_send(fd, event, data) declaration

  chttp.c
  - chttp_sse_route() — registers a GET route with an sse_handler
  - sse_start() — writes the 200 OK + text/event-stream headers to the raw fd
  - chttp_sse_send() — writes a formatted SSE event (event: ...\ndata: ...\n\n)
  - chttp_dispatch() — new branch: flush headers → call sse_handler(fd) → return -1 (same pattern as WS)

  server.c — handle_sse(int fd)
  - select() with 10-second timeout drives the loop
  - recv(..., MSG_DONTWAIT) on a readable fd detects client disconnect
  - Every tick sends two named events:
    - ping → {"timestamp":"..."}
    - message → {"text":"hello from server","timestamp":"..."}

  Test:
  curl -N http://localhost:8000/sse

  # or in a browser:
  const es = new EventSource('http://localhost:8000/sse');
  es.addEventListener('ping',    e => console.log('ping',    e.data));
  es.addEventListener('message', e => console.log('message', e.data));

